    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but some people say that the UN is basically just a relic that's fundamentally broken because it can't even act when the big powers are involved. do historians see those critiques as valid structural flaws, or do they mostly view the UN's struggles as just an inevitable part of how hard global diplomacy is?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
